    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix heap buffer overflow in phy_sr_indication and related functions\n\n### Summary\nThere is a heap buffer overflow due to incorrect memory management in the phy_sr_indication function and similar functions in nfapi/oai_integration/nfapi_vnf.c. When these functions are called multiple times for the same subframe index, they allocate new memory without freeing previously allocated memory, leading to memory leaks and potential heap corruption.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/nfapi_vnf.c`: \n  - Added memory deallocation checks in `phy_sr_indication()` before allocating new memory\n  - Added error handling for malloc failures\n  - Applied same fixes to `phy_harq_indication()` and `phy_crc_indication()` for consistency\n  - Ensured proper mutex unlocking even in error cases\n\n### Reproduction\nThe issue can be reproduced by running the VNF in a scenario where multiple SR/HARQ/CRC indications are received for the same subframe index before the previous indications are processed and freed by the downstream code. This leads to:\n- Memory leaks\n- Potential heap corruption\n- Segmentation faults under heavy load conditions\n\nThe symptoms include crashes in the VNF when handling multiple simultaneous UE connections with high uplink traffic.\n\n"
}